    "en": {
      "title": "Finland and Sweden officially accede to Noto",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Finland and Sweden formally signed the NATO Accession Protocol, a necessary step in furthering their membership in the alliance.",
        "The protocol must now be ratified by the 30 allied parliaments, allowing both countries to officially become members of NATO.",
        "The signing took place at a meeting at NATO headquarters in Brussels. NATO Secretary General Jens Stoltenberg, who presided over the event, said it was a \"historic\" moment for the alliance.",
        "\"This is a good day for Finland and Sweden and a good day for NATO. With 32 countries around the table, we are stronger as we face the biggest security crisis in decades. It will make our people safer,\" Stoltenberg noted.",
        "The breakthrough came as the three nations agreed to pledge each other's protection after Turkey lifted its veto on the two Nordic countries' bid to join NATO last week."
      ],
